        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 7:00AM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 700 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles northeast of South Dos Palos, or 18 miles
south of Merced, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merced, Madera, Atwater, Los Banos, Chowchilla, Kerman, Livingston,
Mendota, Firebaugh, Delhi, Winton, Hilmar-Irwin, South Dos Palos,
Cantua Creek, Dos Palos, Planada, San Joaquin, Le Grand, Ballico, and
Panoche Road.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
